{
  "stem": "17426.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so it was polite, and it was quasi not obvious and not overt.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But it was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I, as a child, did not feel it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I played with Christian children, with Roman Catholics, with, with Protestants, with Germans, with any other-- Russians.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I did not feel it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "However, when I at the age of 13, when Hitler took power in 1933, things changed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was at many times exposed to certain intimidations, stories that were so anti-Semitic that I could not stomach them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I came home and I asked my parents whether this is true.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they had a hard time to explain me what is the difference between truth and the difference between people making up truths.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That is the time when shortly thereafter, Pilsudksi died and Rydz-Smigly became the president.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And when Rydz-Smigly became the president, the right [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] became more excessive to Rydz-Smigly-- Rydz-Smigly made them more excessive to himself.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And so the accent changed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The character of Jewish-Catholic Polish relations changed very much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "A Jew was not seen as a, as a Polish person.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He was seen as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Even so he was a citizen, he was not regarded as being a citizen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because they felt that in order to be a Polish citizen, you must be Christian first.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say the very year that I mentioned, 1933.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It does not take long for the Polish right to pick up on, pick up on Hitler's ideas.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so they emulated him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They invited-- as a matter of fact, shortly before the war, before the war, they invited Goring for a, for a hunt in Polish woods and played to the Germans, up as best as they could.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They're hoping that they can avoid a war with Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
